The Windswept Plains~
The wind from the mountaintops is strong here, bringing with it an icy
chill that no cloak can guard against.  The mountain’s shadow extends over
the plains, keeping the sun from offering any respite from the bitter wind. 
Though mostly bare of anything taller than a bush, small patches of blue and
red wildflowers add colour and life to the plains, and every now and then a
small field mouse speeds through the grass, wary of predators.  
