#10905
The Unmarked Graves~
The plains continue in every direction, the city of Caerlon visible to
the south and the snow-capped mountains standing out against the horizon to
the north.  Amidst the knee-high grass that grows for miles all around, two
dirt mounds can be seen, hidden from view until they are almost underfoot. 
Stones and pebbles have been piled atop the mounds, marking them as grave
sites, though there is nothing to indicate who lies beneath.  The wind is
hushed here, blowing gently over the graves as if in reverence for those who
have fallen here.  
~
